# configs/common/.gitignore
#
# Sub-directory gitignore for the configs/common/ tree. Lives HERE (not at
# the repo root) so all the rules for this tree are co-located and readable.
#
# Goal: keep ONLY the template file under git control. Everything else
# (real user config with absolute paths, debug files, anything else the
# user creates) MUST be ignored, so machine-specific absolute paths can
# never leak to the public github.com/potterwhite/ArcFoundry repo.
#
# Pattern notes:
#   - `*` ignores everything in this directory (recursively in modern git).
#   - `!.gitignore` keeps THIS file tracked. Without it, the sub-dir
#     gitignore would ignore itself and silently disappear from the repo.
#   - `!rk-toolchain.template.yaml` keeps the template.
#
# What users do:
#   cp configs/common/rk-toolchain.template.yaml \
#      configs/common/rk-toolchain.yaml
#   ...edit the copy...   (the copy is ignored automatically)

*
!.gitignore
!rk-toolchain.template.yaml
